## Supabase (Back Burner)
- Supabase MCP and backend integration are optional for now.
- If/when you enable Supabase later, use it for schema changes and migrations, and never write raw SQL directly.
- All Supabase client calls go in `src/lib/supabase.ts`
- Use TanStack Query for all async data fetching
- Use React Hook Form + Zod for all forms
- Never expose service role keys client-side

## File Structure
```
src/
  pages/       # One file per route (Index, About, Cigars, etc.)
  components/  # Shared components (Navbar, Footer, etc.)
    ui/        # shadcn primitives — DO NOT EDIT
  hooks/       # Custom hooks (use- prefix)
  lib/         # supabase.ts, utils.ts, helpers
  assets/      # Static images
```

## Do Not
- Do not push directly to `main`
- Do not use `console.log` in production code
- Do not hardcode placeholder text — if real content isn't available, use a clearly marked `// TODO:` comment
- Do not create new dependencies without checking if something in `package.json` already solves the problem
- Do not add comments that just describe what the code does — only explain *why* when non-obvious
